description: Byggmax Group AB engages in the retailing of building materials. The company is headquartered in Solna, Stockholm and currently employs 1,121 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2010-06-02. The firm is engaged in the discount retail of construction materials in the Nordic do-it-yourself (DIY) market. Its offering includes basic construction materials, such as wood, stone and concrete, isolation materials, doors, windows, flooring, paints and coatings, tools, screws, bolts, basic electrical and ventilation materials, kitchen and toilet fittings, as well as wooden cottage sets. The firm operates Byggmax Norge and Byggmax AB Finland as subsidiaries responsible for retail sails in Norway and Finland, as well as Buildor AB and Skanska Byggvaror as wholly owned subsidiaries. Its largest shareholder is Altor 2003 Sarl, which holds 35.76% of the Company’s shares. The firm operates 67 stores across Sweden.
